                <h1>Why Chinua Achebe Wrote "Things Fall Apart"</h1>
                <p>Chinua Achebe wrote "Things Fall Apart" to depict the impact of British colonialism and cultural collision on African societies, specifically the Igbo community. He aimed to present an authentic African perspective, countering stereotypes in Western literature. The novel explores themes of identity, tradition, and change, reflecting on the complexities of post-colonial identity.</p>
